RECAP
Average percent of workloads deployed in cloud has nearly doubled in last year,
and is expected to hit the tipping point in 12 months.
1
2
Mission-critical workloads account for more than 50% of cloud deployments today on average,
and with 2/3rds investing in new mission-critical cloud applications continued growth is likely.
3
8 out of 10 report cybersecurity concerns are limiting cloud usage but fewer than 10%
report known security incidents linked to cloud.
5
Majority trust public cloud solutions to keep data secure, at least for some applications,
but only a minority are comfortable storing most healthcare data in the public cloud.
4
Data theft, compliance and identity access management are key cloud security concerns
but fewer than 50% are taking steps to mitigate these concerns.
For more information about the Center for Connected Medicine,
